The move advances NEP 2020’s early skills vision. Here’s the schedule, key venues and what schools must implement—timetable hours, projects, assessment and the year-end Kaushal Mela.
title: CBSE to train teachers for mandatory skill education from Jan 5: Check key details

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump and First Lady Melania hosted their annual New Year's Eve party at Mar-a-Lago, with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu among the high-profile guests. Trump's New Year's resolution was "Peace on Earth." The event included a charity auction where a painting sold for $2.75 million.
title: Charity auction, Netanyahu among partygoers: Inside Trump and Melania’s Mar-a-Lago New Year’s Eve party

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold price prediction: According to Abhilash Koikkara of Nuvama Professional Clients Group, MCX Gold is expected to maintain its positive bias unless there is a clear and decisive break below the 132,000 support level.
title: Gold & silver price prediction: What's the outlook for New Year? Top things to know

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Indian-origin Zohran Mamdani was sworn in as New York City's first Muslim mayor early Thursday, beginning a four-year term. The 34-year-old Democrat took the oath at the City Hall subway station, with a larger public ceremony to follow. Mamdani, known for his left-leaning views, previously served in the New York State Assembly.
title: Indian-origin Mamdani sworn in as New York City first Muslim mayor at historic subway station — watch

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The CIA has refuted Russia's claim that Ukraine attempted to attack President Vladimir Putin's residence, a statement echoed by US officials. President Trump, initially troubled by the accusation, later acknowledged a lack of confirmation. This incident follows a meeting between Trump and Ukrainian President Zelenskyy, where progress on peace talks remained limited.
title: Ukraine drone plot against Putin: US intelligence rejects Russian claim — What the CIA says

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Banks across India will observe several closures in January 2026 due to national and regional holidays. Several states will see bank branches shut on dates ranging from January 2nd to January 26th, with Republic Day impacting most of the country. Customers are advised to plan physical transactions in advance, as digital services remain accessible.
title: Bank holidays in 2026: When will banks remain closed in January? Check list

author: SUHAS NAYSE
description: Batting at No. 4, Sarfaraz Khan blasted nine fours and 14 sixes, bringing up his hundred off just 56 balls. His innings left Goa’s bowlers and fielders looking shellshocked. On Wednesday, he delivered it with a sledgehammer, scoring a blistering 157 off 75 balls to power Mumbai to a 87-run victory over Goa at the Jaipuria Vidyalaya Ground.
title: 'Dreams don't come true that quickly': Sarfaraz Khan after blistering 157 off 75 balls

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Mumbaikars welcomed the New Year 2026 with unexpected heavy showers and drizzle across several parts of the city on Thursday morning. The unseasonal rains, which began shortly before 6 am and gradually reduced, made the weather pleasant for many residents. Social media users shared their surprise and appreciation for the beautiful, albeit unusual, weather.
title: Mumbai receives surprise morning showers on 1st day of 2026

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The Indian Rupee began 2026 on a weak footing, depreciating significantly against the US dollar due to sustained foreign fund outflows and trade uncertainties. Despite India's steady growth, capital flows have faltered, making the rupee vulnerable. Analysts anticipate continued volatility, with the currency facing pressure from global investor caution and tariff disruptions.
title: Rupee enters New Year 2026 in red: Falls 11 paise to 89.99 against US dollar

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Joshua was tr​avelling on Monday with Sina Ghami and Latif Ayodele on a busy highway linking Lagos and Ibadan in southwestern Nigeria when their SUV crashed into a stationary truck. The Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Agency (TRACE) in Ogun state, where the accident occurred, said preliminary investigations showed the vehicle suffered a tyre burst before ramming into the truck.
title: Two friends killed: Ex-boxing champion Anthony Joshua survives fatal car crash - Watch

author: MAZHAR ALI
description: Chandrapur police have busted a pan-India kidney trafficking ring with international ties, implicating two specialist doctors from Delhi and Trichy. The racket, involving illegal transplants in India and abroad, was exposed by a debt-ridden farmer. Investigations reveal a well-organized network of agents, donors, and hospitals, with transplants priced between ₹50 lakh and ₹80 lakh.
title: Pan India kidney racket exposed: Police names doc in organ trade; int'l links probed

author: SHALABH
title: Ram’s ideals guided Operation Sindoor: Rajnath Singh

author: SAHIL MALHOTRA
description: Ajit Agarkar has been repeatedly questioned about the omission and has maintained the "need to play some cricket" stand. If 145.2 overs in Ranji Trophy, 26.5 overs in Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy and 34.2 overs in ongoing Vijay Hazare Trophy doesn't qualify, then the definition of "some cricket" needs to be made clear.
title: India vs New Zealand | Fit and firing: Why Agarkar & Co. can't ignore Shami anymore

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India and New Zealand are set for an eight-match limited-overs series, including three ODIs and five T20Is, from January 11 to 31. This series is crucial for senior players returning to the ODI setup and for finalising T20 combinations ahead of the 2026 T20 World Cup. While the BCCI has already announced the T20I squad for the New Zealand series, the ODI squad is yet to be named.
title: India vs New Zealand ODI squad announcement: Date, where to watch - All you need to know

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in green on the first trading session of the New Year 2026. While Nifty50 went above 26,150, BSE Sensex was up over 100 points.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 opens above 26,150; BSE Sensex up over 100 points

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Contaminated drinking water has led to a severe outbreak of diarrhoea and vomiting in Indore's Bhagirathpura area, resulting in at least seven deaths and over 1,100 residents falling ill. Officials have acknowledged lapses, leading to the suspension of several municipal corporation employees. The incident has raised serious questions about civic oversight despite the city's 'cleanest city' reputation.
title: Water contamination kills 7: Crowned cleanest city 8 times, Indore now faces tap-water crisis

author: SAURABH SINHA
title: Duty breach: AI pilot detained at Vancouver airport after failing breath test

author: TNN
description: Delivery workers across India observed a New Year's Eve strike protesting low pay and lack of social security, despite app-based platforms offering festive bonuses. While many customers remained unaware, several orders faced significant delays. Platforms like Swiggy and Zepto increased per-order pay, but some workers refused the incentives, citing unachievable targets and the risk of ID blocking.
title: Gig workers' stir: Riders say accidents, shrinking payouts drove strike call

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi and President Droupadi Murmu conveyed New Year wishes for 2026. They prayed for peace, good health, and happiness across society. The nation welcomed the year with vibrant celebrations. Fireworks lit up cities as people gathered to mark the fresh beginnings of 2026 with enthusiasm and cheer.
title: New Year 2026: PM Modi greets nation, prays for 'peace and happiness in society'

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi woke to dense fog and 'very poor' air quality with AQI at 372, impacting visibility and traffic. Unfavorable meteorological conditions are expected to keep pollution levels high for the next six days. Despite a slight annual PM2.5 decline, the polluted season saw a rise, with Delhi remaining the most polluted city in the NCR.
title: New Year, same air: Delhi starts 2026 with ‘very poor’ AQI at 372; Anand Vihar worst hit

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Top stock market recommendations: Aakash K Hindocha of Nuvama Professional Clients Group recommends buying BHEL, IOC, and Gujarat Mineral Development Corporation. He also shares his views on Nifty and Bank Nifty.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for January 1

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: As 2025 drew to a close, Smriti Mandhana took to Instagram on December 31 to share a recap video of the year gone by. The video featured glimpses of her World Cup-winning celebrations, cherished moments with her family, and snippets from her fitness routine. What stood out, however, was the quote she chose to end the video with—a line attributed to Lord Krishna from the Bhagavad Gita.
title: Smriti shares cryptic Gita quote in year-end post after calling off wedding

author: MAHIMA ROY
description: Stefon Diggs and Cardi B have been dragged into a new drama as the star player's new baby mama has alleged that she is pregnant with his child again. Aileen Lopera has sued Stefon Diggs for the second time as the star player is already involved in a messy legal trouble with his former private chef who has accused him of physical violence.
title: Who is Aileen Lopera? Stefon Diggs’ alleged baby mama amid Cardi B's silence

author: etimes.in
description: The new year arrives without fanfare, prompting a moment of reflection before sending messages. The article offers simple, honest phrases for New Year's greetings, acknowledging that not everyone starts the year with grand plans. It emphasizes genuine connection and self-compassion over forced cheerfulness, encouraging a quiet, hopeful approach to the year ahead.
title: 75+ Happy New Year messages, greetings, wishes and quotes for 2026

author: TNN
description: A key suspect in the murder of Bangladeshi Islamist radical Sharif Osman Hadi has denied involvement and refuted claims he fled to India. Faisal Karim Masud, identified as a primary suspect by Bangladesh, stated in a video message from Dubai that he is not involved in the killing and was forced to leave Bangladesh due to false implications.
title: 'I'm in Dubai,' says Hadi killing suspect Dhaka accused India of sheltering

author: DHANANJAY.MAHAPATRA
description: Chief Justice Surya Kant has introduced a new system to prioritize cases for the disadvantaged. Petitions from disabled individuals, acid attack survivors, senior citizens over 80, those below the poverty line, and legal aid recipients will now be fast-tracked. This initiative aims to ensure their cases don't get overlooked amidst the Supreme Court's massive caseload.
title: SC handled 75k cases in 2025; unmatched by any top court
